-- Samaras Wants Greek Asset-Sale Amendments This Month, Real Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-08-11T16:06:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-11/samaras-wants-greek-asset-sale-amendments-this-month-real-says.html
Greek Prime Minister Antonis Samaras
told government ministers to complete work this month on 77
amendments to be included in a bill that aims to speed up state
asset sales,  Real News  reported, without citing anyone.  One of the amendments will be the abolition of a
requirement for the state to keep a minimum stake in companies
considered of strategic importance, the Athens-based newspaper
reported in a preview of an article to be published in
tomorrowâ€™s edition.  Companies affected by the amendments include  Public Power
Corp. SA (PPC) , which Samaras wants to split into smaller companies,
 Opap SA (OPAP) ,  Hellenic Petroleum SA (ELPE) , Athens Water Supply & Sewage Co.
SA, Thessaloniki Water Supply & Sewage SA,  Piraeus Port
Authority (PPA)  SA,  Thessaloniki Port Authority SA (OLTH) , Depa SA and Desfa
SA, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
